1. Consistency of the interaction (if the item needs to slide, it doesn't get stuck, nor is it hard to stop; if the item needs to be touched, i can expect it to work without having to fiddle with how much pressure I'm applying),
2. sensitivity to input (i don't want to really have to press really hard on something that goes on my phone, nor do I want the object to register being in my pocket as touch),
3. clarity of feedback (if I have to slide stuff around, I would like a soft click to tell me when I am going through the positions, similarly to how I would like some physical resistance to buttons so I know that I am pressing down correctly); 
4. responsiveness under different weather conditions (I would like to be able to use the object if it's drizzling, or if I am wearing gloves)
5. discretion (having to take out a syringue and fill an object with water means that the object if completely useless on the bus, or literally anywhere that is not a lab)
